 A 72-hour Activation Plan has been mobilised by the National
Commissioner of Police, General Khehla Sitole, following the killing of a
Lieutenant Colonel at Ndwedwe, north of Durban, KwaZulu-Natal, on Monday
evening. Police spokesperson, Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo, said the
Acting Station Commander of Ndwedwe police station, Lieutenant Colonel Jabulani
Ndawonde Â (56) was driving to his home
when at about 6.30 pm on Monday he was gunned down near the Bhamshela Taxi
Rank. Naidoo said it has been established from preliminary
investigations that unknown occupants travelling in mini pick-up truck opened
fire on Ndawonde as they passed his vehicle. Ndawonde died at the scene. While the Provincial Commissioner of KwaZulu-Natal has
mobilized the 72-hour Activation Plan, Naidoo said police are appealing to
anyone who has any information on who may be responsible for this crime contact
them. Information may be communicated via the SAPS Crime Stop
number 086 00 10111 or via the MySAPSApp, an application which can be
downloaded on any iPhone or Android. All information will be treated with strictest confidence,
said Naidoo. 